<li id="cite_note-43"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-43">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFStewart1962">Stewart (1962</a>)</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-44"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-44">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">There are some similarities in this line of thinking with <a href="../Ian_F._Hancock" title="Ian F. Hancock" class="mw-redirect">Hancock's</a> domestic origin hypothesis.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-45"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-45">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Wittmann (1983, 1995, 2001), <a href="#CITEREFFournier1998">Fournier (1998</a>), <a href="#CITEREFFournierWittmann1995">Fournier &amp; Wittmann (1995</a>); cf. the article on Quebec French and the History of Quebec French</span></li>
